Endometriosis causing cyclic compression of the right external iliac vein with cyclic edema of the right leg and thigh. A case report of endometriosis encircling the right external iliac vein, causing catamenial edema of the right leg and thigh, is presented. Successful surgical treatment is described. A literature review of extraperitoneal endometriosis will further the reader's awareness of unusual presentations of endometriosis.